HEADWORD: Holmos
<hw>Hol"mos</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr.<?/.]</ety> <fld>(Greek & Etrus. Antiq.)</fld> <def>A name given to a
vase having a rounded body</def>; esp.: <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A closed
vessel of nearly spherical form on a high stem or pedestal.</def>
<au>Fairholt.</au> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A drinking cup having a foot and
stem.</def>⟦br⟧
